<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911107-0153</DOCNO><DOCID>911107-0153.</DOCID><HL>   Technology:   Celtrix Plans to Buy BioGrowth</HL><DATE>11/07/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   CTRX</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>MEDICAL andamp; BIOTECHNOLOGY, GENETIC RESEARCH, PROSTHETICS (MTC)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   PALO ALTO, Calif. -- Celtrix Laboratories Inc. said itsigned a definitive agreement to acquire BioGrowth Inc., aclosely held concern in Richmond, Calif., for about $14million of newly issued shares.   Celtrix said it expects to complete the acquisition inDecember but that the deal is subject to the approval ofBioGrowth's shareholders. The resulting company will becalled Celtrix Pharmaceuticals Inc. and will be based in newfacilities in Santa Clara, Calif.</LP><TEXT>   Both companies are developing products based oncell-regulating proteins.</TEXT></DOC>